24/06/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- Serbia-Montenegro Defence Minister Prvoslav Davinic made a historic visit to Albania on Wednesday (23 June), the first of its kind in 57 years. He met with senior officials, including President Alfred Moisiu. Kosovo and military co-operation were among the issues discussed. Albanian Defence Minister Pandeli Majko invited the Serbia-Montenegro Army to observe drills by the Albanian Navy. Officials pledged to bolster bilateral relations, which had soured during the Milosevic era. (Albanian Daily News, ATA, Tanjug - 23/06/04)
